Are South Africans going to rescue our state coffers by paying higher taxes? eNCA's Heidi Giokos has more. #eNCA​ #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Finance Minister will deliver his budget for the year on Wednesday. However, the question is - are South Africans going to rescue our state coffers by paying higher taxes? If you are dreading tax increases in this budget, you will probably have to swallow a bitter pill. The money has got to come from somewhere. READ: Youth unemployment is a desperate challenge - expert Experts agree your income probably won't be targeted, and value-added tax is also unlikely to be a preferred option for Treasury. The virus-hit economy and tax-fatigued consumers won't be able to tolerate further hikes. Watch the video above for more detail on this story.